{
  "id": "L15",
  "title": "At the Doctor's Office",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "In this lesson, you will learn how to talk to a doctor about your symptoms. First, let's learn how to check in for your appointment."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L15_E01",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Buenos días",
        "meaning": "Good morning"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V01",
      "data": {
        "una cita": "an appointment"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L15_E02",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Tengo una cita",
        "meaning": "I have an appointment"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "To say that you have a symptom, you can use the verb `Tener` (to have). The 'I' form is `tengo`."
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V02",
      "data": {
        "dolor de cabeza": "headache"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L15_E03",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Tengo dolor de cabeza",
        "meaning": "I have a headache"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V03",
      "data": {
        "tres días": "three days"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L15_E04",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Desde hace tres días",
        "meaning": "For three days"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L15_P01",
      "data": {
        "word": "cita",
        "phonetic": "see-tah",
        "tip": "In many Spanish-speaking regions, the 'c' before 'i' or 'e' sounds like an 's'."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L15_S01",
      "title": "Checking In",
      "setting": "You arrive at the doctor's office. First, you speak to the receptionist, then to the doctor.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Greet the receptionist and state your purpose",
          "chatbot_message": "Buenos días."
        },
        {
          "title": "Explain your main symptom",
          "chatbot_message": "Hola, soy el doctor. ¿Qué pasa?"
        },
        {
          "title": "Say how long you have had this problem",
          "chatbot_message": "Entiendo. ¿Desde cuándo?"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Great start! Now let's learn how to describe more symptoms and answer the doctor's questions."
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V04",
      "data": {
        "también": "also"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V05",
      "data": {
        "fiebre": "fever"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L15_E05",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "También tengo fiebre",
        "meaning": "I also have a fever"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "To say a part of your body hurts, use `Me duele` followed by the body part, like `Me duele la cabeza`."
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V06",
      "data": {
        "la garganta": "the throat"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L15_E06",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Me duele la garganta",
        "meaning": "My throat hurts"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L15_E07",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "He tomado",
        "meaning": "I have taken"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V07",
      "data": {
        "paracetamol": "paracetamol"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L15_P02",
      "data": {
        "word": "garganta",
        "phonetic": "gar-gan-ta",
        "tip": "The 'g' sound here is hard, like in the English word 'go'."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L15_S02",
      "title": "Answering Questions",
      "setting": "The doctor continues to ask you questions about your symptoms.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Describe another symptom",
          "chatbot_message": "¿Algo más?"
        },
        {
          "title": "Answer where it hurts",
          "chatbot_message": "Entendido. ¿Le duele la garganta?"
        },
        {
          "title": "Say what you have already taken",
          "chatbot_message": "De acuerdo. ¿Ha tomado algo?"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Excellent. Finally, let's learn how to understand the doctor's advice and conclude the appointment."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L15_E08",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "¿Puede repetir, por favor?",
        "meaning": "Can you repeat, please?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V08",
      "data": {
        "más despacio": "more slowly"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V09",
      "data": {
        "necesito": "I need"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V10",
      "data": {
        "una receta": "a prescription"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L15_E09",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "¿Necesito una receta?",
        "meaning": "Do I need a prescription?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L15_E10",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Muchas gracias",
        "meaning": "Thank you very much"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L15_P03",
      "data": {
        "word": "receta",
        "phonetic": "reh-seh-ta",
        "tip": "The 'r' at the beginning of a word is often rolled slightly in Spanish."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L15_S03",
      "title": "Understanding Advice",
      "setting": "The doctor gives you some advice. You need to understand it and ask for a prescription before leaving.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Ask the doctor to repeat slowly",
          "chatbot_message": "Bueno, necesita descansar y beber mucha agua."
        },
        {
          "title": "Ask if you need a prescription",
          "chatbot_message": "Claro. Usted... necesita... descansar."
        },
        {
          "title": "Thank the doctor",
          "chatbot_message": "No, no necesita una receta."
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}